<br>
Make sure that you buff with SoW deep (damage shield too) during your blue buffing phase, then keep two instant click items on top of it so he can't dispell. <br>
<br>
At the beginning of the fight unload an entire golem wand on him. Stay in close, out of melee but under bow range. It's very difficult to maintain but otherwise you get hit by the bow. If he has a @#%$ bow or isn't using it between rounds don't bother and just joust normal. Come in to attack and backstab or to interrupt spells. If he trueshots just stay in close.<br>
<br>
Keep your MR at least at 100 to keep him from snaring you. Keep your FR up. Wear a fungi.<br>
<br>
Basically, if you can keep SoW and DS up after dispelling him you'll win because there's a good chance a blue server dueler won't have instant dispell. Luckily you came to us, so you know better.<br>
<br>
This should be a very easy fight. Rangers don't become overly difficult till they start gearing up really well.<br>
<br>
There's more in my post in the library. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufilash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filash</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0> at: 1/30/02 9:01:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upickkpockket999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pickk Pockket999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/1/02 8:49:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=579.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling an epic Ranger, do I have a chance?</span><hr size=1> If you are willing to pull out all the stops a ranger is actually one of the easier classes to beat (in my opinion. I haven't fought any with post epic weapons and full NToV gear yet).<br>
<br>
1: Like everyone said get yourself some golem wands. They drop in the second gator pool in Cazik thule off of the steel golem. If you spend a day there you will walk away with 4-5 golem wands.<br>
<br>
2: Buy a shaman sow potion. Almost no rangers have J-Boots, altough they might have AA run speed 3. There is currently a bug where if you dispell their sow they will slow down to normal run speed for a tick. This could be really useful.<br>
<br>
3: Use a shaman dmg shield potion. He probably is so you should too.<br>
<br>
4: You have mrylokar right? Ok, here is what you do. First things first give yourself Ultravision, then an illusion of your choice, then storm strength, then if you have it a shrunken goblin earing buff (this is invaluable since you will be going at shaman sow speed you can't use J-Boots as your quick buff to slow dispells. This item fills that roll.). Now buy a fire resist potion from a potion vendor, put that on next and finally your dmg shield potion followed by your sow potion.<br>
<br>
5: Get yourself a stack of pre-nurf pummice. This is great because you can use it to dispell yourself one buff at a time. If not use regular pummice. Click off Ultravision and Illusion if you have the goblin earning. That leaves your top 2 buff slots open so when he casts dots or god forbid a snare (this should never ever happen) on you, you can easily dispell it.<br>
<br>
6: Get your MR up there. A vampire blood from Mistmoore would work wonders here. MR gear is easy to obtain and you should have no problem getting around 100+ mr. Fire resistance you want about 85ish at least.<br>
<br>
7: Apply a good muscle lock type poison. I usually find that they don't stick on anyone anyways but what the heck its worth a shot.<br>
<br>
8: Get your friendly neighbourhood mage to summon you a levitation ring.<br>
<br>
9: Lastly have everything hotkeyed. You don't want to be fumbling through your inventory looking for stuff.<br>
<br>
When the fight starts open up with your golem wands. I find 5 clicks of one will usually do the trick, altough your milage may vary. Make sure the dmg shield chat filter is left to all so you can see if he still has his up. Hope the poison lands and go to work on him, circling for backstabs. He will most likely try to get some room on you, but you are faster than him now so stick to him like glue. <br>
<br>
Try and fight him near the colums on the edges of the arena. This is so if he does get room and you see trueshot get activated you can use a very cheesy trick. Click on your levitation ring and walk up one of the columns. Due to the &quot;Your target is too far above/below you&quot; bug he will be unable to land a single bow shot on you. While trueshot is up, bandage up some of your wounds up there and apply another poison. Then go back down and finish off the kill.<br>
<br>
Note: Do not joust a ranger. They have excellent dmg output with bows and AA points. It is simply not worth it if they know what they are doing. Also if you can't get lev off try and get your body either as close to him as possible or as much of it into a wall surface as possible. There is a bug that if a certain % of you is stuck in a wall trueshot will miss every time.<br>
<br>
<br>
Hope this helps <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upickkpockket999.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pickk Pockket999</A> at: 2/1/02 8:52:36 am<br></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15>The Arena</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
